  <render>
    <tex>%text
If $A$ is a square matrix such that $A^2=I$ (Identity matrix) then,
%
\begin{align}
  (A-I)^3+(A+I)^3-7A=A
\end{align}</tex>
  </render>
  <reason>
    <tex>\begin{align}
  &amp;(A-I)^3+(A+I)^3-7A \\
  =&amp;2A^3+6AI^2-7A \\
  =&amp;2A+6AI^2-7A \quad (\because A^2=I) \\
  =&amp;2A+6A-7A \quad(\because MI=M) \\
  =&amp;A
\end{align}</tex>
  </reason>
